<h4 style="color: #DAA520;">Closed Beta: Patch 32 (July 9th, 2014)</h4><ul><li>Fixed a bug where this item was unintentionally reducing the damage from magical damage applied from basic attacks (Kensu Q, Zalgus W, Vex W and Faris Q)</li></ul><h4 style="color: #DAA520;">Closed Beta: Patch 28.1 (April 24, 2014)</h4><ul><li>The Toughness Stackable Passive on this item will now be half as effective as the previous stack, rather than half as effective as only the first. The values will be as follow for stacking multiple Toughness Stackable Passives (6->3->1.5...) instead of (6->3->3...).</li></ul><h4 style="color: #DAA520;">Closed Beta: Patch 27 (March 17, 2014)</h4><ul><li>The flat basic attack damage reduction granted by this item's Stackable Passive (Toughness I) is now only doubled against Shapers, rather than tripled.</li></ul><h4 style="color: #DAA520;">Closed Beta: Patch 26.1 (March 3, 2014)</h4><ul><li>The Stackable Passive - Toughness I will now be 50% as effective for every stack beyond the first.</li></ul><h4 style="color: #DAA520;">Closed Beta: Patch 26 (Feb 24, 2014)</h4><ul><li>The Toughness I passive is now stackable.</li><li>Now builds into the new Advanced item: Form.</li><li>Now builds into the new Advanced item: Resolve</li></ul>